                <div class="container-fluid">
                    
                </div>
            </section>
            
            <!-- Widgets Added Here -->
            
            <section class="home-about" id="section-video">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="offset-sm-1 col-sm-10 offset-lg-0 col-lg-12">
                            <h2 class="text-center text-h-mort wow fadeIn pb-4 pt-lg-4" style="font-size: 36px">Videos</h2>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="container-fluid">
                    
                </div>
            </section>
            <!-- Widgets End Here -->
            <section class="mb-0 pb-240">
                <div class="container-fluid">
                    
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="text-section pb-240">
                <div data-jarallax-element="-150" class="text-section-box"></div>
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row text-row">
                        <div class="col-lg-6 pt-lg-5">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What can you expect from a Vampire Facial in Houston?</h3>
                                <p>
                                    Houston Vampire Facials are great for treating and improving a variety of skin conditions. Many people consider Vampire Facials for treatment of wrinkles and fine lines, reducing large pores, reducing the appearance of scars from acne and trauma, correcting sun damage, evening skin tone, and rejuvenating tired-looking skin. A Vampire Facial is designed to improve the overall health of your skin, as well as improving specific problem areas.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What procedures are often performed with a Vampire Facial in Houston?</h3>
                                <p>
                                    Vampire facials include either microneedling or microdermabrasion as part of the procedure. This preparation of the skin allows the platelet-rich plasma serum to deeply penetrate the skin and encourage healthy cell growth and activity below the surface of the skin.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    If you want to reduce the appearance of wrinkles, <a href="/fillers-houston">fillers</a> can be included as part of the procedure. The plastic surgeons at The Oaks Plastic Surgery in Houston work with a variety of filler treatments and will find the perfect solution for your skin goals.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-lg-6">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What can you expect on the day of your Vampire Facial?</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">                                    
                                     Since a Vampire Facial uses your blood as a basis for the platelet-rich plasma serum, your Vampire Facial will begin with a blood draw. A single vial of blood is drawn from your arm. Your doctor will then use a centrifuge to separate the platelets from the other parts of the blood.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    Next, your face will be cleaned thoroughly and you will undergo a microneedling or microdermabrasion procedure. This step clears away dead skin and allows for maximum penetration of platelets into your skin. Finally, the PRP serum will be applied and allowed to absorb into your skin.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3></h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">

                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What can you expect for recovery after your Vampire Facial?</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    You should expect some redness and tenderness in the treated areas after the procedure. This can last from anywhere from 24 hours to a week, depending on your skin’s reaction to the procedure and the amount of microneedling required for your particular goals. 
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    Generally, patients recover more quickly from a Houston Vampire Facial than other skin-resurfacing treatments, because the PRP serum helps to speed healing. While your skin is healing from your Vampire Facial procedure, you’ll need to be careful of sun exposure.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    The process of microneedling creates tiny channels in the skin that help topical treatments better penetrate the various layers of skin. Certain skin care products can be used to support and enhance your Vampire Facial treatment after your session. This also means you need to be cautious about applying anything other than physician-recommended skin care products during the healing phase.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
